{"id":3819,"date":"2015-08-26T20:20:02","date_gmt":"2015-08-26T20:20:02","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/?page_id=3819"},"modified":"2019-12-17T21:05:47","modified_gmt":"2019-12-17T21:05:47","slug":"family-roles-addiction-drug-rehab-therapy-sandy-utah","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/family-roles-addiction-drug-rehab-therapy-sandy-utah\/","title":{"rendered":"Family Roles in Addiction &#8211; Drug Rehab Therapy in Sandy, Utah"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignright wp-image-3823\" src=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/3_gen_beach-e1440617128483.jpg\" alt=\"family roles in addiction - Pathways Real Life Recovery\" width=\"327\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/3_gen_beach-e1440617128483.jpg 1000w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/3_gen_beach-e1440617128483-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/pathwaysreallife.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/08\/3_gen_beach-e1440617128483-360x240.jpg 360w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 327px) 100vw, 327px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>What Are the Family Roles in Addiction?<\/h2>\n<h3>Addiction affects every member of a family!<\/h3>\n<p>Drug and alcohol\u00a0abuse\u00a0is a <strong>complex problem because it negatively affects both the addict and their loved ones<\/strong>. At Pathways Real Life Recovery, we help the individual battle addiction and go as far as helping the family affected by the addiction as well. Our methods of therapeutic support and education help empower families, which leads the addict toward a healthy recovery by fixing the family&#8217;s foundation to improve on their overall quality of life. As the methods for addict recovery are unique for all families, our Utah therapists tailor their treatments to adhere to the root of the addiction so the addict can overcome the source of the addiction. Given the collateral damage that comes along with an addiction, <strong>it&#8217;s important that the entire family gets the help and support they need to overcome problems rooted in addiction<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>Family is a very helpful tool towards tackling an addiction, with therapy providing help and support &#8211; that both parties need &#8211; for a healthy future. In situations of addiction, it may require medication, residence treatment, and family therapy by the learning steps on how to empower their loved ones.<\/p>\n<h2>The Benefits of Family Treatment for Substance Abuse<\/h2>\n<h3>Tackle substance abuse as a family!<\/h3>\n<p>Family substance abuse and treatment therapy benefits on many levels. It treats the family member in need of help as well as each family member that has been affected by the addiction. <strong>When the addict is presented with the effects of their problem\u00a0in therapy, it puts their issues into perspective and lays down the groundwork for a better future with their loved ones.<\/strong> In addition to this, a therapy group offers some insight into the struggles an addict faces and how they can bounce back with their family on their side. Given the wide range of advantages, family therapy towards substance abuse and addiction is an excellent decision for an excellent outcome.<\/p>\n<h2>With Help from a Utah Therapist, Your Family Can Combat Addiction<\/h2>\n<h3>Here&#8217;s what we&#8217;ll help your family do:<\/h3>\n<div style=\"margin-left: 15px;\">\n<div class=\"su-list\" style=\"margin-left:0px\">\n<ul>\n<li><i class=\"sui sui-chevron-circle-right\" style=\"color:#4d7599\"><\/i> <strong>Asking About It &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0If you didn&#8217;t care, you wouldn&#8217;t be\u00a0seeking therapy. By offering\u00a0support, it\u00a0helps to assure them that they&#8217;re not alone in the battle and you want to help as well.<\/li>\n<li><i class=\"sui sui-chevron-circle-right\" style=\"color:#4d7599\"><\/i> <strong>Discovery &#8211;<\/strong> Family therapy opens new doors for communication that not only benefit everyone involved but make the challenges less staggering to overcome.<\/li>\n<li><i class=\"sui sui-chevron-circle-right\" style=\"color:#4d7599\"><\/i> <strong>Fixing Relationships &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Family therapy helps repair, build, and strengthen relationships that may have been damaged as a result of the addiction.<\/li>\n<li><i class=\"sui sui-chevron-circle-right\" style=\"color:#4d7599\"><\/i> <strong>Strengths &amp; Weaknesses &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Family therapy allows a group to acknowledge their strengths and work on their weaknesses.<\/li>\n<li><i class=\"sui sui-chevron-circle-right\" style=\"color:#4d7599\"><\/i> <strong>Address Issues &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Family therapy allows the group to comfortably address their issues in a safe and civil manner.<\/li>\n<li><i class=\"sui sui-chevron-circle-right\" style=\"color:#4d7599\"><\/i> <strong>Family Roles &#8211;<\/strong>\u00a0Family therapy allows a group to examine\u00a0their roles, behavior patterns, and rules for self-growth.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<h3>Learn More About Family Roles in Addiction Treatment<\/h3>\n<h4>Call Pathways for a free assessment today!<\/h4>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" style=\"margin-right: 10px;\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/phuEvnBppUc\" width=\"320\" height=\"240\" frameborder=\"0\" align=\"left\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"><\/iframe> Pathways Real Life Discovery is here to not only make life\u00a0enjoyable, but assist those who may need some help or guidance on their journey. Once given the tools and skills in family therapy, a family can focus on being a family&#8230; that&#8217;s stronger than ever before.<\/p>\n<p>If you or a loved one are suffering from an addiction, come get the help you need from Pathways Real Life Recovery.<strong> Learn more today about your family roles in addiction by setting up a free consultation with our addiction specialists<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<div>\n<div>